metadata.name: Hydro Gen #51
metadata.description:
Against the backdrop of texts about valuing water, Hydro Gen charts the ecological devastation and eventual revival of the Tisza river following what has been called one of the gravest environmental disasters in central Europe since Chernobyl.

Nature and humans here are bound within a single frame â€” havoc in the ecological system activates the breakdown of meaning in the human signifying system of language, but hidden in the wave of ecological disaster is a (re)generative love poem to water that bears witness to its multifaceted beauty and power. A second poem is generated as a soundtrack based on the displayed background text.

- - - - - CLICK TO START SOUND - - - - -

Hydro Gen is a collaborative work conceptualized and developed over the course of one week as part of NFT DEB Generative Dimensions 2022 Hackathon and Conference.

Kalen Iwamoto, lead artist, director

Vitalii Shumanskyi, lead programmer

Nayven Vignette, audio programmer

metadata.name: interval composition study #5
metadata.description:
interval composition study

exploring Plato's idea in Symposium, paraphrasing: "it is beauty I seek, not beautiful things"

the principles of forms ::: searching for balance and beauty in the randomness

starting with composition studies - rule of thirds, varying intervals, and golden rectangle/mean support

using base colours & base/Platonic forms - switched to mostly monochrome to build up tones, with a splash of red to add emphasis/focus

main image is fullscreen view - best viewed in fullscreen view
the different previews will show cropped view

drawing by AliaK 16/12/2022

coded in p5.js

metadata.description:

Click â€œsâ€

Resolution:
Default image width = 2000px and aspect ratio = 4:3.
Modify the image width between 2000px and 10000px by adding â€œ&w=xxxxâ€ to the url (e.g. &w=4000).
High resolutions are computationally expensive and may take a while.

Background:
The canvas background texture is visible by default. This can be toggled off by adding â€œ&b=0â€ to the url.
The background scales with resolution to mimic a bigger canvas so it will look different at different resolutions.
At high resolutions a MoirÃ© pattern may appear on the canvas background texture due to the way images are resized in the browser. Itâ€™s always recommended to download a full resolution version of the piece.

metadata.name: Poem Of Atoms #38
metadata.description:
There is a force in the universe that binds everything together
It's a electronic web that connects everything in a delicate balance. 
Some call it fate. But few know the truth.
They are the lifeblood of our society, and they are what keep us moving forward. We are constantly surrounded by them, and they are always changing. It's not a force, it's an orbit. And the dots are the energy sources.

Made with P5js

metadata.name: Oscillators #278
metadata.description:
Click anywhere on the oscillator to play/pause.

3 Rules of Oscillators:
RULE 1, Oscillators should be viewed on Desktop (this is due to the way an oscillator is formed, it requires the display density of the device to be 2 pixels).
RULE 2, Oscillators should be viewed live and not as static images.
RULE 3, Oscillators should be run with the sound on.

Press "S" to Save a version of the Canvas (must be in fullscreen mode)

You are in a dark cave in the Johto region, the year is 1999...

Two synthesizers play a graceful melody atop the shimmering sound of a french horn. A cello provides a deep and haunting counterpoint.

Created with Tone.js and p5js.

Thank you to https://github.com/nbrosowsky/tonejs-instruments for the french horn and cello samples.

metadata.name: BLEND #163
metadata.description:
Blend are generative loops and animated pieces creating a shape with a digital painting effect.
The size, position and motion frequency of trails are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 
You can press spacebar to stop the animation.

Created by Quentin HocdÃ©, in Brussels (Belgium).â€¨â€¨

Features :
	- Between 10 and 80 trails, impacted or not by an update of their radius and randomly filled
	- 4 directions - from North West (NW), from North East (NE), from North or from West.
	- Duration between 16 and 24 seconds
	- Amplitude of the shape on X and Y
	- Offset delay: between 0.1 and trails count, manage the delay between each trails movement
	- Noise count : number of points to create the noise effect on background
	- Background color :  color randomly get from 1 of 151 color themes

metadata.name: BWEEPS  #232
metadata.description:
A minimalist, black-and-white generative profile picture (PFP) created to commemorate one-year anniversary of Bwople project by Gengoya. The artwork is derived from an initial sketch of Bwople which, despite being not the one that was chosen, still managed to captivate interests. The project provides a unique glimpse into an alternate universe in which Bwople could have been represented.

All images are hand-drawn work by Gengoya and composed by Vector Recite using PureSpider's fxhash-pfp maker tool.

To download the full size image on fx(hash):
- Click "open" below the image
- Left click on the image, a "Download image" button will appear on the bottom right.
- Click the "Download image" button.
